To fix the Lofree Block keyboard (in Windows mode) on XFCE (tested on Devuan) :

Open a text editor with root privileges to create a new driver config file:
    sudo mousepad /etc/modprobe.d/hid_apple.conf

Paste this into the file to force standard F-key behavior:
    options hid_apple fnmode=2

Save the file and close the text editor.

Update the boot image so it remembers this rule:
    sudo update-initramfs -u

Restart your computer.
